<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title><%= title %></title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css" />

  <!-- Google Font: Playfair Display -->
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400..900;1,400..900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  <script src="https://public.flourish.studio/resources/embed.js"></script>
  <style>
    .flourish-container {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .graph-info {
      display: none;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="container mt-5">

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <div class="hero-section text-center">
    <h1 class="text-primary mb-3">
      A Taste of the Skies:<br>
      Exploring Airline Meal Diversity Over Enschede
    </h1>
    <p class="text-secondary">
      (Yes, Dutch airline food continues to disappoint)<br>
      <p class="text-tertiary">
      ("Even in the sky" - Ana)
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-primary mb-1"></h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Each day, a wide array of aircraft traverse the skies above Enschede, carrying not only passengers but a rich tapestry of cultures, 
      cuisines, and national identities. This project dives into the hidden stories behind those flights — from the most common airlines 
      passing overhead, to the meals they serve, their countries of origin, and the types of food offered onboard. 
      By visualizing this data, we uncover how Enschede’s skies reflect a vibrant mix of international travel and taste.
    </p>
    <p class="sub-text">
      Made by Group 24: Ana Antohi, Juliette Gelderland, Andrea Otero Arraez, Claudia Huanca Armaza
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="section-divider">

  <!-- Row 1: Graph on left, text on right -->
  <div class="row align-items-center mb-5 section-alt">
    <div class="col-md-7">
      <div class="flourish-container">
        <div class="flourish-embed flourish-hierarchy" data-src="visualisation/23562391"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
      <h4 class="info-heading">Who's Flying — and What's Cooking?</h4>
      <p class="info-text">
        Ever looked up and wondered who's flying overhead — and what’s being served onboard? 
        This packed bubble chart reveals the countries and airlines most frequently flying over Enschede, 
        along with the meals they offer. Click through each layer: from country → airline → specific dish — 
        and uncover the culinary story behind the skies.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="section-divider">

  <!-- Row 2: Text on left, graph on right -->
  <div class="row align-items-center mb-5 section-alt">
    <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
      <div class="flourish-container">
        <div class="flourish-embed flourish-map" data-src="visualisation/23562757"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
      <h4 class="info-heading">Global Tastes at Cruising Altitude</h4>
      <p class="info-text">
        This chart uncovers which countries' airlines are most likely to serve which category of meals. 
        By linking meal descriptions to airline origins, we get a glimpse into culinary preferences across borders – 
        revealing who’s bringing poultry and who's bringing fish to the skies above Enschede.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="section-divider">

<!-- Row 3: Graph on left, text on right -->
<div class="row align-items-center mb-5 section-alt">
  <div class="col-md-7">
    <div class="flourish-container">
      <div class="flourish-embed flourish-chart" data-src="visualisation/23563393"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-5">
    <h4 class="info-heading">Sky-High Pricing: Comparing In-Flight Meal Costs by Airline</h4>
    <p class="info-text">
      Meals at 30,000 feet can range from budget bites to premium plates. 
      This graph compares airline meal prices, highlighting how different airlines approach in-flight catering costs.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

  <hr class="section-divider">

  <!-- Row 4: Text on left, graph on right -->
  <div class="row align-items-center mb-5 section-alt">
    <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
      <div class="flourish-container">
        <div class="flourish-embed flourish-hierarchy" data-src="visualisation/23622792"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
      <h4 class="info-heading">Veg or Meat at 30,000 Feet?</h4>
      <p class="info-text">
        Ever wondered whether your in-flight meal came from a farm or a field?
This sunburst chart reveals the food categories served by airlines flying over Enschede — and whether they’re vegetarian or meat-based.
Start at the center with the type of food, then spiral out to the airlines, and finally to specific dishes.
Use the filter to explore the skies through a dietary lens: is your airline offering more greens or more wings?
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>